The paper deals with the computational complexity of push-pull block puzzles, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The problem involves moving objects on a grid, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the connections between push-pull block puzzles and reversibility, which could make it relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
